The game conveys  subtle lessons:
- how to deal with betrayal ;
- loyalty needs boundaries ;
- any individual that speaks some amount of French willingly is an asshole.

Borderlands: The Pre-Sequel is a first-person shooter with great RPG elements and addictive gameplay set in the orbit of Pandora. I think it is the most underrated game in the Borderlands franchise. It is not perfect, of course, but compared to Borderlands 2 it has a lot of improvements and cool ideas. I highly recommend it to anyone who wants to experience the amazing origin story of one of the best villains.

Pros:
- Great arsenal;
- Great soundtrack and voice acting;
- Smooth and responsive controls;
- Good optimisation;
- Great enemy variety;
- Unique setting and environment;
- Memorable cast of characters;
- Claptastic Voyage is one of the best DLC in the franchise (IMHO);
- Awesome story;
- Great character progression;
- Fun gameplay;
- Replayability;
- Awesome location design;
- Great boss fights;

Cons:
- Humor is very hit-and-miss;
- Gunplay is generally mediocre;
- Low-grade equipment is useless;
- Compared to Borderlands 2, much less content;
- Too much referencing instead of worldbuilding;
